WEBVTT

00:01.422 --> 00:02.923
OKAY, WE'RE ALL BOARDED UP
FOR THE STORM.

00:02.923 --> 00:04.335
[ THUNDERCLAP ]
AH! AND IT LOOKS GREAT.

00:04.335 --> 00:06.677
I AM LOVING
ALL THE NEW ARTWORK, JULES.

00:06.677 --> 00:09.720
THANKS. I THOUGHT I'D MAKE
HURRICANE PREP FUN.

00:09.720 --> 00:12.633
THAT ONE'S MY FAVORITE.
IT'S LIKE TOM IS RIGHT HERE.

00:12.633 --> 00:15.096
Tom: I AM!
IT'S PRETTY NASTY OUT HERE! AAH!

00:15.096 --> 00:16.477
Grayson: WHOA!
Andy: OH, HO HO!

00:16.477 --> 00:18.899
OH, THAT WIND IS VICIOUS.

00:18.899 --> 00:20.811
YEAH, BUT NOT AS BAD
AS THE GROCERY STORE.

00:20.811 --> 00:22.603
THERE WAS ONLY ONE PACK
OF TOILET PAPER LEFT,

00:22.603 --> 00:26.237
AND ME AND THIS CRAZED HOUSEWIFE
REACHED FOR IT AT THE SAME TIME.

00:26.237 --> 00:28.239
TELL ME
YOU TOOK THAT BITCH DOWN.

00:28.239 --> 00:30.030
[ WIND WHISTLING ]

00:30.030 --> 00:31.992
HA!
[ CLAPS HANDS ]

00:31.992 --> 00:35.496
STILL...I FEEL LIKE
THERE'S SOMETHING MISSING.

00:35.496 --> 00:38.209
ARE YOU PERHAPS LOOKING FOR...
THESE?

00:38.209 --> 00:40.040
OHH!
AAH!

00:40.040 --> 00:41.832
YEAH!

00:41.832 --> 00:43.794
YOU ARE ALMOST SEXY
RIGHT NOW.

00:43.794 --> 00:45.756
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY?
I GOT BIT.

00:45.756 --> 00:47.088
MMM.

00:47.088 --> 00:50.091
в™Єв™Єв™Є

00:52.133 --> 00:53.514
Jules: UGH.

00:53.514 --> 00:55.766
THAT WAS A WILD NIGHT,
BUT WE MADE IT THROUGH.

00:55.766 --> 01:00.101
AND NOBODY BEHAVED BADLY EXPECT
FOR EVERYTHING THAT JELLY DID.

01:00.101 --> 01:01.772
I WARNED YOU GUYS --

01:01.772 --> 01:04.395
WHEN I FEAR FOR MY LIFE,
I KICK AND SCREAM AND YELL

01:04.395 --> 01:06.357
AND I TELL PEOPLE EXACTLY WHAT
I THINK ABOUT THEM.

01:06.357 --> 01:10.651
STILL, I AM SORRY
FOR EVERYTHING THAT I SAID.

01:10.651 --> 01:12.113
AND DID.

01:12.113 --> 01:15.326
I'D BE MAD
IF I WASN'T SO IMPRESSED.
UGH.

01:15.326 --> 01:17.198
HOW IS THE DAMAGE OUT THERE?

01:17.198 --> 01:18.659
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE WE LOST
A TREE

01:18.659 --> 01:21.001
AND GAINED A NEW PATIO SET!

01:21.001 --> 01:22.963
SCORE!

01:26.797 --> 01:28.969
YOU'RE HOLDING HANDS?
WHAT, IS THE WORLD ENDING?

01:28.969 --> 01:31.552
NO, IT'S JUST ALL THE CHAOS
AND DESTRUCTION IN TOWN

01:31.552 --> 01:34.305
MAKES ME FEEL ROMANTIC.

01:34.305 --> 01:36.056
IF WE HAD WALKED OVER
A POWER LINE,

01:36.056 --> 01:38.179
ANDY MIGHT'VE GOTTEN LUCKY
RIGHT THERE AND THEN.

01:38.179 --> 01:39.850
OOH! [ LAUGHS ]

01:39.850 --> 01:41.522
WOW, SOUNDS LIKE
THE POWER'S STILL OUT

01:41.522 --> 01:43.184
ALMOST EVERYWHERE IN TOWN.

01:43.184 --> 01:45.146
A PIPE BURST AND FLOODED
THE GYM AT THE HIGH SCHOOL,

01:45.146 --> 01:47.107
AND THEY WERE HAVING
THEIR PROM TONIGHT.

01:47.107 --> 01:48.489
SO I CALLED THE SCHOOL
AND I SAID,

01:48.489 --> 01:49.940
"PROM'S ON TONIGHT,
FREE OF CHARGE,

01:49.940 --> 01:51.402
RIGHT HERE AT GRAY'S PUB."

01:51.402 --> 01:52.943
[ LAUGHS ]
YEAH.

01:52.943 --> 01:54.405
LAUGH IT UP.
I HAVE TO CLOSE THE BAR EARLY

01:54.405 --> 01:56.076
AND FILL IT WITH STREAMERS
AND BALLOONS

01:56.076 --> 01:58.999
FOR A BUNCH OF KIDS WHO AREN'T
PAYING A DIME. [ LAUGHS ]

01:58.999 --> 02:00.501
IT'S SO FUNNY.
SUCKS TO BE YOU RIGHT NOW.

02:00.501 --> 02:02.293
IT DOES. [ GASPS ]

02:02.293 --> 02:05.206
OH, JULES, IS THERE A SMALL
DETAIL YOU MIGHT'VE LEFT OUT?

02:05.206 --> 02:07.338
I SIGNED US ALL UP
AS CHAPERONES.

02:07.338 --> 02:09.380
OH. THEY DON'T SEEM
VERY EXCITED.

02:09.380 --> 02:10.921
I'M SURE THEY'LL BE BETTER
WHEN THEY REALIZE

02:10.921 --> 02:12.673
THEY CAN JUST STAND AROUND
AND DRINK ALL NIGHT.

02:12.673 --> 02:15.135
OH. WELL...
OH! THEY CAN'T!

02:15.135 --> 02:17.308
BECAUSE THE HIGH SCHOOL'S
MAKING ME TAKE ALL THE LIQUOR

02:17.308 --> 02:19.600
OUT OF MY BAR FOR THE NIGHT!

02:21.222 --> 02:23.814
IT'LL BE FUN?
I WILL KILL YOU.

02:23.814 --> 02:28.189
THIS WHOLE PROM IDEA
IS SO LAME, RIGHT?

02:28.189 --> 02:30.731
WELL, IT DEPENDS ON
WHO YOU WERE IN HIGH SCHOOL --

02:30.731 --> 02:32.903
A PASTY YOUNG DORK
WITH MORE ZITS THAN FRIENDS,

02:32.903 --> 02:35.236
OR A DASHING BABEHOUND
WITH DANCE MOVES SO SMOOTH

02:35.236 --> 02:37.778
THEY ALMOST SENT A TEACHER
TO JAIL.

02:37.778 --> 02:39.620
MRS. PRITCHETT LOVED MY DANCING
SO MUCH

02:39.620 --> 02:43.494
THAT SHE ASKED ME OVER TO
GIVE HER A DANCE LESSON. HMM.

02:43.494 --> 02:46.417
I WASN'T READY TO DO THE KIND OF
DANCING SHE WANTED TO DO.

02:46.417 --> 02:49.590
WOW. HIGH SCHOOL ME
WOULD'VE HATED HIGH SCHOOL YOU.

02:49.590 --> 02:52.002
IF WE'RE DOING THIS,
WE SHOULD DO IT RIGHT.

02:52.002 --> 02:54.755
CHAPERONES ARE
PROM SECRET SERVICE.

02:54.755 --> 02:57.598
IT'S LIKE I KEEP TRYING TO TELL
YOU, BOO -- STOP TALKING TO ME.

02:57.598 --> 02:59.059
LOOK, TONIGHT WON'T BE
SO BAD.

02:59.059 --> 03:00.931
ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS STAND AROUND.

03:00.931 --> 03:02.473
I'M GONNA ACT LIKE I DID
AT MY OWN PROM --

03:02.473 --> 03:05.566
I'LL BE ALOOF AND ABOVE IT ALL
AND JUDGE EVERYONE.

03:05.566 --> 03:07.938
YOU'LL SEEM DIFFERENT, BUT NOT.
YEAH.

03:07.938 --> 03:09.940
GUYS, NONE OF US ARE GONNA
TAKE THIS THAT SERIOUSLY --

03:09.940 --> 03:12.363
I NOW TAKE THAT BACK.

03:13.864 --> 03:16.487
[ to tune of "Bridal Chorus" ]
в™Є PROM, PROM, PROM-PROM в™Є

03:16.487 --> 03:18.949
в™Є PROM, PROM, PROM-PROM в™Є

03:18.949 --> 03:21.282
[ GASPS ] PROM!

03:21.282 --> 03:22.663
YIKES.

03:22.663 --> 03:25.085
DUDES. WEAK.

03:25.085 --> 03:28.088
HOW COME I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO'S IN THE PROM SPIRIT?

03:28.088 --> 03:30.090
'CAUSE YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
INSANE ENOUGH

03:30.090 --> 03:32.753
TO THINK THAT WE'RE GONNA
JUMP ABOARD YOUR CRAZY TRAIN.

03:32.753 --> 03:35.296
ELLIE, I CAUGHT SOME OF THAT,
AND I DON'T THINK I LIKED IT.

03:35.296 --> 03:36.927
YOU KNOW WHAT SUCKS?

03:36.927 --> 03:39.139
THE FACT THAT I'M THE ONLY ONE
THAT IS WEIRD ENOUGH

03:39.139 --> 03:41.262
AND GOOFY ENOUGH TO TAKE THIS
AS A CHANCE

03:41.262 --> 03:42.973
FOR US ALL TO HAVE A LITTLE FUN
OURSELVES.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.895
THAT'S WHAT SUCKS.

03:44.895 --> 03:46.807
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]
O...M...

03:46.807 --> 03:49.440
GIGI FREAKIN' FERNГЎNDEZ!

03:49.440 --> 03:51.231
[ BOTH GIGGLE ]

03:51.231 --> 03:54.064
MY BABY HAS NO SHOT
AT A NORMAL LIFE.

03:54.064 --> 03:55.856
в™Є PROM-PROM-PROM, PROM
PROM-PROM-PROM, PROM, PROM в™Є

03:55.856 --> 03:57.318
I THINK IT'S SWEET.

03:57.318 --> 03:58.949
THE CAR'S OUT FRONT
WHEN YOU'RE READY.

03:58.949 --> 04:01.782
AAH! OH!
[ GIGGLES ]

04:05.165 --> 04:06.787
YOU'RE WELCOME.
WE'RE SO GLAD YOU CAME.

04:06.787 --> 04:08.749
NOW GO GET CRAZY! IT'S PROM!

04:08.749 --> 04:11.001
WHOO! PROM!

04:11.001 --> 04:14.295
IF THESE KIDS GET HALF AS CRAZY
AS I DID AT MY PROM...

04:14.295 --> 04:17.468
TELL ME ABOUT IT. THE THINGS
THAT WENT DOWN AT MY PROM...

04:17.468 --> 04:20.551
в™Єв™Єв™Є

04:20.551 --> 04:22.383
PLEASE DON'T GET PREGNANT!

04:22.383 --> 04:24.555
SOMETIMES "I LOVE YOU" IS JUST
A TRICK TO GET YOUR DRESS OFF!

04:24.555 --> 04:26.096
[ SIGHS ] LAURIE, YOU KNOW,

04:26.096 --> 04:27.768
I THOUGHT I'D BE THE ONLY ONE
GETTING DRESSED UP.

04:27.768 --> 04:30.351
BUT THEN THERE YOU WALK IN,
LOOKING AMAZING.

04:30.351 --> 04:32.353
A LITTLE SLUTTY,
BUT MOSTLY AMAZING.

04:32.353 --> 04:35.656
YOU, TOO. WHEN I WALKED IN
AND I SAW YOU IN THIS DRESS,

04:35.656 --> 04:38.569
I WAS LIKE, "AH! SOUL MATES!

04:38.569 --> 04:40.030
YOU KNOW,
SINCE THE DAY WE MET,

04:40.030 --> 04:42.242
I SPENT MOST OF
MY CRAZIEST TIMES WITH YOU.

04:42.242 --> 04:44.665
OH! LIKE THE TIME WE BROKE
ALL THE PENISES OFF THE STATUES?

04:44.665 --> 04:46.116
[ LAUGHS ]
OR WHEN WE WENT BAR HOPPING

04:46.116 --> 04:47.908
AND WE STOLE
THAT SCARY COP'S GUN?

04:47.908 --> 04:49.410
[ GASPS ] OR WHEN WE BROKE INTO
TOM'S HOUSE

04:49.410 --> 04:51.171
AND WE LOCKED HIS GIRLFRIEND
IN THE CLOSET?

04:51.171 --> 04:52.873
WOW.
WE SOUND TOTALLY INSANE

04:52.873 --> 04:54.335
WHEN YOU STRING 'EM
ALL TOGETHER.

04:54.335 --> 04:55.716
YOU READY FOR ANOTHER
CRAZY ADVENTURE?

04:55.716 --> 04:57.177
THE CRAZIER, THE BETTER!

04:57.177 --> 04:59.470
[ LAUGHS ]
[ LAUGHS ]

04:59.470 --> 05:01.301
SO, LIKE, NORMALLY,
THIS IS THE MOMENT

05:01.301 --> 05:02.973
WHERE I WOULD POUND MY DRINK AND
THEN SMASH IT AGAINST THE WALL,

05:02.973 --> 05:04.425
BUT I'M KIND OF
AT A LOSS HERE.

05:04.425 --> 05:07.097
WOULD THESE HELP?
[ GASPS ]

05:07.097 --> 05:08.479
SOUL MATES!

05:08.479 --> 05:10.391
PARTY IN THE BATHROOM STALL,
Y'ALL!

05:10.391 --> 05:12.643
OH! ISN'T IT GREAT THAT
YOU CAN STILL GET CRAZY

05:12.643 --> 05:14.485
WHEN YOU'RE A MOM?

05:16.777 --> 05:18.359
IT'S TIME TO PUT
THE POPULAR GIRLS

05:18.359 --> 05:19.900
IN THEIR PLACE.

05:19.900 --> 05:22.282
HEY, CATTY CHEERLEADERS,
YOU WANT SOME REAL GOSSIP?

05:22.282 --> 05:25.406
YOUR JOCK BOYFRIENDS ARE
ALL IN LOVE WITH EACH OTHER.

05:25.406 --> 05:28.158
ELLIE, I AM TRYING TO FOCUS
ON MY JOB.

05:28.158 --> 05:30.411
ME, TOO. YOU THINK THIS
DUMB PROM'S GONNA MOCK ITSELF?

05:30.411 --> 05:31.872
PROM IS NOT DUMB!

05:31.872 --> 05:33.504
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL NIGHT
OF MAGIC AND WONDER.

05:33.504 --> 05:36.126
AND SOMETIMES, A POOR KID'S LIFE
IS DESTROYED FOREVER.

05:36.126 --> 05:38.338
BUT THAT WON'T HAPPEN HERE.

05:38.338 --> 05:41.221
OH, NO! NOT ON MY WATCH!

05:41.221 --> 05:44.224
IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU'RE
WORKING THROUGH SOME STUFF.

05:44.224 --> 05:45.726
I'M GONNA LEAVE YOU TO IT.

05:45.726 --> 05:48.429
AND I GOTTA GET BACK
TO MY THANG.

05:48.429 --> 05:51.351
HEY, BET YOU 5 BUCKS
THAT 5 YEARS FROM NOW,

05:51.351 --> 05:54.855
THAT CONDOM WILL STILL
BE IN YOUR POCKET.

05:54.855 --> 05:59.440
YOU GET IT.
HE'S NOT GONNA EVER USE IT.

05:59.440 --> 06:00.981
IT'S NOT THAT HEAVY.

06:00.981 --> 06:02.533
DO I NEED TO MAKE FUN
OF "STAR WARS" OR SOMETHING

06:02.533 --> 06:05.406
TO SUMMON
YOUR ANGRY NERD STRENGTH?
I'M FINE.

06:05.406 --> 06:06.907
[ Strained voice ] AND ANYONE
WHO MAKES FUN OF "STAR WARS"

06:06.907 --> 06:08.949
IS JUST REVEALING THEIR OWN
CINEMATIC IGNORANCE.

06:08.949 --> 06:11.662
[ CHUCKLES ] NERD SPEAK.
WHOA.

06:11.662 --> 06:13.494
I DON'T REMEMBER HAVING THAT
IN MY STOREROOM.

06:13.494 --> 06:16.707
YO, GUYS. WHAT'S GOING ON?
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:16.707 --> 06:18.208
WHY AREN'T YOU
OUT AT THE PARTY?

06:18.208 --> 06:21.672
THE THING IS...
WE'RE IN A WEIRD SITUATION.

06:21.672 --> 06:24.134
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

06:24.134 --> 06:25.556
I GET IT, FELLAS.

06:25.556 --> 06:28.008
IT'S OKAY.
I MEAN, LOOK, YOU'RE 17.

06:28.008 --> 06:29.810
LIFE'S CRAZY RIGHT NOW,

06:29.810 --> 06:32.513
AND THE ONE THING YOU CAN REALLY
COUNT ON IS YOUR BEST FRIEND.

06:32.513 --> 06:34.685
IT'S NATURAL TO KISS A LITTLE.

06:34.685 --> 06:37.107
YOU KNOW, JUST SEE
IF IT FEEL ALL RIGHT.

06:37.107 --> 06:38.569
DUDE!

06:38.569 --> 06:40.320
WE'RE NOT GAY. WE DIDN'T KISS.

06:40.320 --> 06:42.282
UH, DUH!

06:42.282 --> 06:43.944
[ LAUGHS ]

06:43.944 --> 06:45.656
I DID NOT KISS MY BEST FRIEND
IN HIGH SCHOOL EITHER.

06:45.656 --> 06:47.407
AT ALL. EVER.

06:47.407 --> 06:50.581
WE ARE ALWAYS PULLING BACK
A STRANGE NEW LAYER ON YOU,

06:50.581 --> 06:52.202
AREN'T WE?

06:52.202 --> 06:55.586
THIS IS JUST THE GREATEST NIGHT!
ISN'T IT, LAURIE?

06:55.586 --> 06:59.249
[ DROWNERS' "A BUTTON
ON YOUR BLOUSE" PLAYING ]

06:59.249 --> 07:01.502
HOW LONG HAVE WE BEEN
HOLDING HANDS?

07:01.502 --> 07:03.133
HUH. WASN'T THAT FUN?
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:03.133 --> 07:05.756
WHY DON'T YOU GO SPEND SOME TIME
WITH YOUR FRIENDS NOW?

07:05.756 --> 07:08.348
[ GASPS ]
THESE KIDS ARE SO HAPPY.

07:08.348 --> 07:10.100
THEY EVEN GAVE ME
A NICKNAME --

07:10.100 --> 07:12.813
"THAT LADY WHO SAVED PROM."
[ LAUGHS ]

07:12.813 --> 07:14.645
I EVEN MADE
A LOVE CONNECTION.

07:14.645 --> 07:16.977
I FOUND A LONELY GUY
AND A LONELY GIRL,

07:16.977 --> 07:20.230
I PUT 'EM TOGETHER...
AND NOW THEY'RE DANCING.

07:20.230 --> 07:21.692
IT'S A WEIRD DANCE.

07:21.692 --> 07:23.023
IT'S LIKE THEY'RE TRYING
TO SMOTHER A FIRE

07:23.023 --> 07:24.485
BETWEEN THEIR CROTCH.

07:24.485 --> 07:26.366
SO WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN DOING
SINCE I LOST YOU?

07:26.366 --> 07:27.738
GETTIN' CRAZY?

07:27.738 --> 07:29.409
YEAH. NO, I MEAN, I WAS.

07:29.409 --> 07:31.872
BUT THEN I REMEMBERED THAT
I LEFT MY PURSE OVER HERE

07:31.872 --> 07:35.576
SO I CAME TO FIND IT.

07:35.576 --> 07:37.337
THAT'S THE END OF THE STORY.

07:37.337 --> 07:39.580
HEY, IT'S EARLY.
LET'S GO HAVE SOME FUN.

07:39.580 --> 07:41.922
GO WITHOUT ME BECAUSE I NEED
TO CATCH MY BREATH

07:41.922 --> 07:44.795
AFTER ALL THE...
PURSE EXCITEMENT.

07:44.795 --> 07:46.507
NO WAY! WE'RE A TEAM!

07:46.507 --> 07:47.968
ALSO, YOU MAY HAVE TO
RESCUE ME

07:47.968 --> 07:50.140
IN CASE ANYONE PULLS ME INTO
A DANCE CIRCLE.

07:50.140 --> 07:51.892
THAT IS MY BIGGEST FEAR.

07:51.892 --> 07:53.894
WELL, THAT AND...
[ Whispers ] CLOWNS.

07:53.894 --> 07:56.356
WHAT ABOUT A DANCE CIRCLE
MADE UP OF CLOWNS?

07:56.356 --> 07:59.189
OOH.

07:59.189 --> 08:04.404
в™Є WHY DON'T YOU JUST
COME AROUND в™Є

08:04.404 --> 08:09.279
в™Є AND UNDO ANOTHER BUTTON
ON YOUR BLOUSE? в™Є

08:09.279 --> 08:11.702
Boy: [ in distance ]
IT'S GOING DOWN.

08:11.702 --> 08:13.323
AT 11:00 SHARP,

08:13.323 --> 08:15.826
WE SHANK THE DORK.

08:15.826 --> 08:20.250
в™Є I HATE THE THOUGHT OF
YOU MISSING OUT в™Є

08:20.250 --> 08:22.212
WHO -- WHO SAID THAT?!

08:22.212 --> 08:23.624
NO.

08:23.624 --> 08:26.717
OH, PLEASE, NO.

08:26.717 --> 08:28.468
SO WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:28.468 --> 08:29.930
ALL RIGHT, SO THERE'S
THIS GIRL HERE TONIGHT

08:29.930 --> 08:32.222
THAT I REALLY LIKE.
SAME WITH ME.

08:32.222 --> 08:34.685
OH, THAT'S GREAT!
PERFECT WINGMAN SITUATION.

08:34.685 --> 08:36.266
TWO BROS, TWO BABES --

08:36.266 --> 08:37.808
YEAH, IT'S THE SAME GIRL.

08:37.808 --> 08:39.399
OHH, THAT IS LESS GREAT.

08:39.399 --> 08:40.941
HER NAME'S KIM.
SHE'S NEW AT OUR SCHOOL.

08:40.941 --> 08:44.194
I'M REALLY INTO HER, SO I ASKED
PETE TO GO TALK TO HER

08:44.194 --> 08:46.146
AND FIND OUT HER SITUATION.
SO I DID.

08:46.146 --> 08:47.738
I WENT UP AND ASKED HER
IF SHE HAD A BOYFRIEND,

08:47.738 --> 08:50.450
AND SHE SAID, "I DO NOW,"
AND THEN SHE WINKED AT ME.

08:50.450 --> 08:52.152
TRAITOR!
I DIDN'T MEAN
FOR IT TO HAPPEN.

08:52.152 --> 08:53.784
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, GUYS.

08:53.784 --> 08:56.206
NO NEED TO LET A GIRL GET
IN BETWEEN TWO BEST FRIENDS,

08:56.206 --> 08:58.118
ESPECIALLY WHEN THERE'S
AN OBVIOUS ANSWER.

08:58.118 --> 08:59.580
VERY OBVIOUS.

08:59.580 --> 09:01.792
THIS ONE GOES TO PETE.
ADAM.

09:03.123 --> 09:05.586
NO, DUDE, THAT IS ADAM.

09:05.586 --> 09:07.588
DUDE, THAT IS PETE.

09:08.839 --> 09:11.511
CAN YOU GIVE US A SEC?

09:11.511 --> 09:13.473
LIVE IT UP, FOOTBALL JOCKS!

09:13.473 --> 09:15.806
IT'S ALL DOWNHILL FROM HERE.
OH!

09:15.806 --> 09:17.808
IT'S GOING DOWN!
I JUST HEARD!

09:17.808 --> 09:19.770
HERE, TONIGHT!
IT'S GOING DOWN!

09:19.770 --> 09:21.812
NICE DRESS.
DID YOUR MOM MAKE IT?

09:21.812 --> 09:23.604
LISTEN TO ME, DAMN IT!

09:23.604 --> 09:26.146
I DIDN'T SEE THEM,
BUT I HEARD THEIR PLAN.

09:26.146 --> 09:28.278
"AT 11:00 SHARP,
WE SHANK THE DORK."

09:28.278 --> 09:31.612
ELLIE, SOME POOR KID'S
GETTING PANTSED!

09:31.612 --> 09:34.655
NO, THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.
NOT NOW! NOT AGAIN!

09:34.655 --> 09:38.248
BOO, YOU GOT YOUR CRAZY FACE ON.
A-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

09:38.248 --> 09:41.291
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]
1987. SENIOR PROM.

09:41.291 --> 09:42.753
I WAS SO EXCITED.

09:42.753 --> 09:44.625
I HAD A COOL TUX,
A HOT DATE,

09:44.625 --> 09:47.127
AND A PLAN TO HELP
MY BEST PAL BUCKY MARTIN

09:47.127 --> 09:49.670
SCORE A DANCE
WITH THE GIRL OF HIS DREAMS.

09:49.670 --> 09:51.551
BUCKY MARTIN?
SOUNDS LIKE A STUD.

09:51.551 --> 09:53.764
HE ACTUALLY WASN'T.
STOP IT.

09:53.764 --> 09:57.097
BUT I KNEW HE COULD BE,
IF HE -- IF HE JUST BELIEVED.

09:57.097 --> 09:58.769
AND THEN WHEN I SAW CINDY LEE

09:58.769 --> 10:01.101
STANDING ALONE
AT THE PUNCH BOWL,

10:01.101 --> 10:02.602
I GRABBED HIM BY THE LAPELS,
I SAID,

10:02.602 --> 10:06.066
"THIS IS IT. YOUR TIME.
BUCKY TIME. GO GET HER."

10:06.066 --> 10:08.939
HE LOOKED SO COOL
WALKING OVER TO HER.

10:08.939 --> 10:11.401
SO BRAVE.

10:11.401 --> 10:14.905
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

10:14.905 --> 10:19.329
SHE LOOKED UP AND SAW HIM
AND SMILED.

10:19.329 --> 10:22.082
в™Єв™Єв™Є

10:22.082 --> 10:24.745
THEY WERE SO FAST.

10:24.745 --> 10:26.206
[ Whispers ] JOCKS ALWAYS ARE.

10:26.206 --> 10:28.418
в™Єв™Єв™Є

10:28.418 --> 10:31.091
IT WAS A HALF A SECOND BEFORE
BUCKY'S PANTS HIT THE GROUND.

10:31.091 --> 10:33.423
[ FABRIC DROPS ]
HE JUST FROZE...

10:33.423 --> 10:35.215
[ LAUGHTER ]
STANDING THERE

10:35.215 --> 10:37.718
IN HIS LITTLE WHITE UNDIES.

10:37.718 --> 10:40.811
THE LAUGHS WERE DEAFENING.

10:40.811 --> 10:45.565
HE TURNED TO ME,
HIS EYES PLEADING FOR HELP,

10:45.565 --> 10:46.977
TREMBLING...

10:46.977 --> 10:48.528
I DID NOTHING!

10:48.528 --> 10:50.610
I COULDN'T EVEN GET OUT
"BUCKY!"
[ GASPS ]

10:50.610 --> 10:52.532
HE TURNED AROUND AND RAN,

10:52.532 --> 10:55.195
HIS PANTS STILL AT HIS ANKLES,

10:55.195 --> 10:57.277
UNTIL HE WAS OUT THE DOOR.

10:57.277 --> 10:59.740
AND I NEVER SAW HIM AGAIN.

10:59.740 --> 11:01.281
UNTIL MONDAY AT SCHOOL,
WHEN I SAW HIM AGAIN.
YEAH.

11:01.281 --> 11:03.123
BUT HE WAS DIFFERENT.

11:03.123 --> 11:05.335
HE WOULD NEVER BE THE SAME.
THE BUCKY I KNEW WAS DEAD.

11:05.335 --> 11:08.208
AND NOW IT'S HAPPENING
ALL OVER AGAIN.

11:08.208 --> 11:09.790
NOT IF WE STOP IT.

11:09.790 --> 11:13.553
I WAS EXCITED ABOUT
MY PROM, TOO.

11:13.553 --> 11:17.677
I HAD THE CUTEST
VINTAGE Y.S.L. JUMPSUIT.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.469
AND WHEN I GOT THERE,

11:19.469 --> 11:21.561
THE NUNS GOT
ALL WEIRD BECAUSE

11:21.561 --> 11:24.564
MY DATE WAS A 28-YEAR-OLD
WALL STREET BANKER.

11:24.564 --> 11:27.477
[ Voice breaks ]
THEY KICKED ME OUT.

11:27.477 --> 11:29.269
I ENDED UP GOING TO
THIS MANSION PARTY

11:29.269 --> 11:32.572
THAT WAS, LIKE, A THOUSAND TIMES
BETTER ALL-NIGHTER.

11:32.572 --> 11:36.276
BUT STILL, I DIDN'T
GET TO DANCE AT MY PROM.

11:36.276 --> 11:37.738
I NEVER KNEW.

11:37.738 --> 11:40.240
I'M SO...[ SIGHS ]

11:40.240 --> 11:42.492
28? REALLY? HE WAS 28?

11:42.492 --> 11:45.205
COME ON. WE HAVE
A MAGICAL NIGHT TO SAVE.

11:45.205 --> 11:47.958
W-WAS IT YOUR DATE'S MANSION?
28?

11:47.958 --> 11:50.961
CHAD, KRISTIN, LOOKIN' GOOD!

11:50.961 --> 11:52.883
THERE'S MY LOVEBIRDS.
[ LAUGHS ]

11:52.883 --> 11:55.255
Tarik Nu Clothes:
в™Є BUBBLE BOOTY в™Є

11:55.255 --> 11:57.097
OOH! THEY MAY NEED A HOSE!

11:57.097 --> 11:59.679
HEY, JULES, MAYBE WE SHOULD
HANG BACK.

11:59.679 --> 12:02.262
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
GIVE THE KIDS SOME SPACE.

12:02.262 --> 12:05.435
THEY LOVE US. WE SAVED PROM.

12:05.435 --> 12:08.688
ALSO, WE'RE SUPER FUN.
I THINK THE KIDS CAN SENSE THAT.

12:08.688 --> 12:11.151
IT'S KINDA LIKE HOW DOGS
CAN HEAR LOUD WHISTLES.

12:11.151 --> 12:17.988
в™Єв™Єв™Є

12:17.988 --> 12:20.160
[ CHEERING ]

12:20.160 --> 12:22.362
DANCE CIRCLE.

12:22.362 --> 12:24.124
[ CHEERING CONTINUES ]

12:24.124 --> 12:26.206
UH, NO, THANKS. I'M GOOD.

12:26.206 --> 12:29.579
I'M NOT REALLY CUT OUT
FOR A DANCE CIRCLE, SO...

12:29.579 --> 12:31.081
Boy: SHAKE IT!
SHAKE IT! SHAKE IT!

12:31.081 --> 12:32.672
BUT JULES AND LAURIE ARE!

12:32.672 --> 12:34.134
WHAT? HOW?

12:34.134 --> 12:35.635
WE'RE GOING IN!

12:35.635 --> 12:37.177
LAURIE, THIS IS WHY
I LOVE YOU!

12:37.177 --> 12:39.049
I CAN DO ANYTHING
WHEN I'M WITH --

12:39.049 --> 12:40.430
LAURIE?

12:40.430 --> 12:41.842
[ GASPS ]

12:41.842 --> 12:43.553
в™Єв™Єв™Є

12:43.553 --> 12:45.806
ALONE IN A DANCE CIRCLE.

12:45.806 --> 12:47.687
NO WAY OUT.

12:47.687 --> 12:50.650
UNLESS I GET TOUGH

12:50.650 --> 12:52.772
AND DANCE MY WAY OUT.

12:52.772 --> 12:58.068
[ CHEERING ]

12:58.068 --> 12:59.449
NO.

12:59.449 --> 13:02.863
I'M GONNA DIE IN HERE.

13:06.246 --> 13:07.747
ALL RIGHT,
WE HAVE TO MOVE FAST.

13:07.747 --> 13:09.209
WE DON'T KNOW
WHO'S BEHIND THIS

13:09.209 --> 13:10.790
AND WE DON'T KNOW
WHO THEIR TARGET IS.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.212
BUT IN A PANTSING PLOT,
THE STORY'S ALWAYS THE SAME.

13:12.212 --> 13:13.713
JERKS VERSUS DORKS.

13:13.713 --> 13:15.175
YOU FIND THE LOSERS HERE
AND GET THEM TO SAFETY.

13:15.175 --> 13:17.047
I'LL SNIFF OUT THE PUNKS
AND THE TROUBLEMAKERS.

13:17.047 --> 13:18.508
BUT MARK MY WORDS,

13:18.508 --> 13:21.011
BY 11:00, ALL DORKS PANTS
WILL BE STANDING.

13:21.011 --> 13:22.552
[ SIGHS ] GOD HELP US.

13:22.552 --> 13:24.224
OH, ELLIE,

13:24.224 --> 13:25.635
WHILE YOU'RE OUT THERE
WADING THROUGH ALL THE JERKS,

13:25.635 --> 13:27.097
PLEASE STAY FOCUSED.

13:27.097 --> 13:28.728
YOU KNOW HOW YOU GET WEAK
AROUND BAD BOYS.

13:28.728 --> 13:31.431
OH, PLEASE.
NO ONE HERE IS OVER 18.

13:31.431 --> 13:34.564
OH, THAT GUY LOOKS
LIKE HE'S OVER 18.

13:34.564 --> 13:36.857
I'LL BE CAREFUL.

13:36.857 --> 13:38.488
WHAT THE HELL?

13:38.488 --> 13:40.861
YOU LEFT ME ALONE
IN A DANCE CIRCLE.

13:40.861 --> 13:42.943
I WAS TRAPPED IN A RING
OF CLAPPING STRANGERS

13:42.943 --> 13:45.655
WHO WOULDN'T LET ME GO
UNLESS I BUSTED A MOVE.

13:45.655 --> 13:47.537
I HAVE NO MOVES TO BUST!

13:47.537 --> 13:49.159
WHAT HAPPENED BACK THERE?

13:49.159 --> 13:51.161
I DON'T EVEN KNOW.

13:51.161 --> 13:53.163
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:53.163 --> 13:56.256
HUH? YOU'VE BEEN ACTING
A LITTLE STRANGE ALL NIGHT.

13:56.256 --> 13:59.259
YOU MADE THAT COMMENT
ABOUT STILL GETTIN' CRAZY

13:59.259 --> 14:00.630
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE A MOM.

14:00.630 --> 14:02.132
IT JUST GOT INTO MY HEAD.

14:02.132 --> 14:04.594
THEN WE WENT INTO THE BATHROOM
TO DRINK,

14:04.594 --> 14:07.928
AND CRAZY GIRLS
IN THESE CRAZY DRESSES...
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:07.928 --> 14:09.970
ABOUT TO POUND
A GIANT BAG OF WINE,

14:09.970 --> 14:12.893
AND I SAW MYSELF
IN THE MIRROR...

14:12.893 --> 14:14.354
[ LAUGHS ] I ONLY SAW
THE CEILING.

14:14.354 --> 14:17.147
I WAS LIKE,
GLUG, GLUG, GLUG.

14:18.398 --> 14:19.980
SORRY. CONTINUE.

14:19.980 --> 14:22.442
I HAVE A BABY AT HOME.

14:22.442 --> 14:24.534
AND HERE I AM,
IN THIS SLUTTY DRESS,

14:24.534 --> 14:27.077
READY TO PARTY MY ASS OFF
IN THE BATHROOM OF A BAR,

14:27.077 --> 14:28.448
ACTING LIKE...

14:28.448 --> 14:30.700
LIKE YOUR MOTHER DID
WHEN YOU WERE A KID?

14:30.700 --> 14:33.873
SHE WAS
THE ULTIMATE PARTY SLUT.

14:33.873 --> 14:35.755
AND THAT'S NOT COMING FROM ME.

14:35.755 --> 14:40.050
THAT WAS AN ACTUAL TITLE
SHE WON IN DAYTONA.

14:40.050 --> 14:42.262
YOU THINK ADAM
SHOULD BACK OFF?

14:42.262 --> 14:44.424
DUH.
CHECK THE MAGIC 8 BALL, BUDDY.

14:44.424 --> 14:47.347
[ GASPS ]
ALL SIGNS POINT TO PETE.

14:47.347 --> 14:49.599
ADAM LIKED KIM FIRST.
WELL, TOO BAD. KIM DIGS PETE.

14:49.599 --> 14:51.181
THAT'S BECAUSE HE STEPPED IN
WITH THE C-BLOCK.

14:51.181 --> 14:53.013
PETE STEPPED IN BECAUSE ADAM WAS
TOO MUCH OF A WUSSY

14:53.013 --> 14:54.894
TO TALK TO KIM HIMSELF!

14:54.894 --> 14:57.317
AHEM.
WE'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

14:57.317 --> 14:58.818
YEAH, YOU GUYS GOOD?
WANT A SODA OR ANYTHING?

14:58.818 --> 15:00.730
Grayson: NO? GREAT.

15:00.730 --> 15:02.692
WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE
LOOKING OUT FOR KIM HERE?

15:02.692 --> 15:04.985
SHE WANTS TALL, COOL PETE,
NOT LAME, WEIRD ADAM.

15:04.985 --> 15:07.237
YOU DON'T KNOW THE FIRST THING
ABOUT ADAM!

15:07.237 --> 15:09.329
YOU DON'T KNOW THE FIRST THING
ABOUT PETE!

15:09.329 --> 15:10.740
HEY, GUYS, DO YOU LIKE
ROLE-PLAYING GAMES

15:10.740 --> 15:13.163
AND STORIES WITH DRAGONS?

15:13.163 --> 15:16.586
GET OUT OF HERE NOW, PLEASE!
RUN FOR YOUR LIVES!

15:16.586 --> 15:19.169
I'M HOSTING A TRUNK SALE
OUTSIDE --

15:19.169 --> 15:20.920
CIGARETTES, BAD LITE BEER,

15:20.920 --> 15:22.963
AND URINE SAMPLES SO CLEAN YOU'D
SWEAR IT WAS FROM THE MATH CLUB.

15:22.963 --> 15:25.675
PARKING LOT. 10 MINUTES.

15:25.675 --> 15:28.308
I THINK I'M HAVING
AN ASTHMA ATTACK.

15:30.430 --> 15:32.852
LEAVE NOW IF YOU VALUE
YOUR PANTS.

15:36.266 --> 15:38.979
JUST GO. GO.

15:40.730 --> 15:43.153
DUDE, THE COPS ARE COMING
TO...[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

15:43.153 --> 15:46.196
I CAN'T LIE TO YOU.
LET'S JUST...

15:46.196 --> 15:49.029
GET IN YOUR CAR AND SEE
WHERE THE NIGHT TAKES US.

15:55.125 --> 15:56.746
LAURIE, YOU'RE NOTHING
LIKE YOUR MOM

15:56.746 --> 15:58.378
AND YOU NEVER WILL BE.
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

15:58.378 --> 16:00.250
WHERE IS YOUR BABY
RIGHT NOW?

16:00.250 --> 16:01.541
AT HOME WITH A SITTER.

16:01.541 --> 16:03.043
WHERE WOULD BABY LAURIE
HAVE BEEN

16:03.043 --> 16:05.135
IF HER MOTHER WAS
OUT AT A BAR, PARTYING?

16:05.135 --> 16:06.636
IN HER PURSE.

16:06.636 --> 16:08.138
AT THE BAR.

16:09.509 --> 16:13.183
JULES, I KNOW
I'M NOT LIKE HER.

16:13.183 --> 16:14.644
I JUST...

16:14.644 --> 16:18.148
I WANNA BE A GREAT MOM
SO BAD THAT...

16:18.148 --> 16:20.770
I'M AFRAID I'M NEVER GONNA
BE ABLE TO HAVE FUN AGAIN.

16:20.770 --> 16:22.692
OF COURSE YOU CAN.

16:22.692 --> 16:24.154
JUST BECAUSE YOU HAVE A KID

16:24.154 --> 16:26.406
DOESN'T MEAN YOU HAVE TO
CHANGE WHO YOU ARE.

16:26.406 --> 16:28.108
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS...

16:28.108 --> 16:29.819
Girl: [ GIGGLES ]
LET'S GO DANCE.
Girl: YEAH!

16:32.492 --> 16:35.245
TRUST YOUR INSTINCTS.
MM.

16:35.245 --> 16:37.617
LAURIE, YOU'RE A MOM.

16:37.617 --> 16:39.879
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE
YOU HAVE A BABY.

16:39.879 --> 16:41.331
IT'S BECAUSE OF WHO YOU ARE

16:41.331 --> 16:44.044
AND THE LOVE THAT YOU HAVE
IN YOUR HEART.

16:44.044 --> 16:46.506
I'VE SEEN THE WAY
YOU HOLD HIM.

16:46.506 --> 16:48.968
AND EVEN WHEN YOU GO OUT
AND YOU GET A LITTLE CRAZY,

16:48.968 --> 16:51.010
THE THING YOU'RE GONNA BE
MOST EXCITED ABOUT

16:51.010 --> 16:53.723
IS TO GET HOME
AND SEE YOUR SON.

16:53.723 --> 16:56.396
ALL MY MOM EVER WANTED TO DO
AT THE END OF THE NIGHT

16:56.396 --> 16:57.937
WAS GO TO AN AIRPORT HOTEL

16:57.937 --> 17:00.140
AND SEE IF ANY HAIR BANDS
WERE STAYING THERE.

17:00.140 --> 17:01.981
SHE ONCE TOOK HER TOP OFF
IN A HOT TUB

17:01.981 --> 17:04.694
AND CAUSED A FISTFIGHT
BETWEEN KIP WINGER

17:04.694 --> 17:06.526
AND THE LEAD SINGER
OF QUIET RIOT.

17:06.526 --> 17:07.987
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME
THAT YOU --

17:07.987 --> 17:09.859
POOLSIDE IN HER PURSE.

17:09.859 --> 17:12.242
IF I CLOSE MY EYES,
I CAN STILL HEAR THEM ARGUING.

17:12.242 --> 17:14.824
MY GOD, SHE WAS NOT
A GREAT MOM.

17:14.824 --> 17:16.116
IT SOUNDED LIKE SHE HAD
GREAT BOOBS, THOUGH.

17:16.116 --> 17:17.707
SHE DID.
MM.

17:17.707 --> 17:19.459
BUT YOU'RE RIGHT, JULES.

17:19.459 --> 17:20.960
THE END OF TONIGHT,

17:20.960 --> 17:23.373
THE THING THAT I AM
MOST LOOKING FORWARD TO

17:23.373 --> 17:25.755
IS GETTING HOME
AND BEING WITH MY BABY.

17:25.755 --> 17:27.377
I KNOW.

17:27.377 --> 17:29.089
COME HERE.
OH.

17:29.089 --> 17:30.430
MM.

17:30.430 --> 17:32.222
JULES...

17:32.222 --> 17:34.514
IS THIS HUG
A DISPLAY OF AFFECTION

17:34.514 --> 17:36.556
OR ARE YOU JUST
DRINKING WINE?

17:36.556 --> 17:39.679
[ Mouth full ]
'SPLAY OF 'FECTION.

17:39.679 --> 17:41.181
ADAM IS NOT LAME.

17:41.181 --> 17:44.023
HE MAY NOT BE TALL
AND GOOD-LOOKING LIKE PETE...

17:44.023 --> 17:46.566
MM-HMM. YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.
BUT -- BUT HE'S DEEP,
INTERESTING, AND HE'S TIRED

17:46.566 --> 17:49.149
OF COOL GUY IDIOTS ACTING LIKE
HE'S INFERIOR.

17:49.149 --> 17:51.151
IF ADAM HAD A FAIR SHOT,
KIM WOULD'VE SEEN HIS SUBSTANCE

17:51.151 --> 17:53.072
AND KNOWN
HE'S THE BETTER GUY.

17:53.072 --> 17:55.785
OH, SO PETE ISN'T SMART AND HAS
NO SUBSTANCE BECAUSE HE'S COOL?

17:55.785 --> 17:58.328
WELL SAID. I AGREE.
THAT IS SO UNFAIR!

17:58.328 --> 17:59.789
COOL GUYS CAN BE DEEP, TOO.

17:59.789 --> 18:01.251
YOU KNOW, YOU CUT THEM,
THEY BLEED.

18:01.251 --> 18:03.002
AND IF YOU CALL THEM DUMB,
THEY HURT.

18:03.002 --> 18:04.874
BUT THEN THEY PUT ON A TANK TOP,
AND EVERYTHING'S OKAY, SO...

18:04.874 --> 18:06.876
UNCOOL GUYS DO NOT HAVE
A MONOPOLY OVER FEELINGS.

18:06.876 --> 18:08.708
HEY, WHERE YOU GUYS GOING?
OUT TO THE PARTY.

18:08.708 --> 18:11.211
WE SETTLED THE KIM THING
ON OUR OWN. WE'RE GOOD.

18:11.211 --> 18:14.344
ALSO, THIS GOT WEIRD WHEN
IT BECAME ABOUT THE TWO OF YOU.

18:14.344 --> 18:16.015
LATER.

18:16.015 --> 18:17.597
ABOUT US? [ CHUCKLES ]

18:17.597 --> 18:19.429
WHAT ARE THEY TALKING ABOUT?
NO IDEA. THEY'RE WEIRD.

18:19.429 --> 18:22.932
TOTALLY. TOTALLY.

18:25.355 --> 18:28.278
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ] IT'S ACTUALLY
A NICE LITTLE PARTY.

18:28.278 --> 18:30.280
YEAH. YEAH, YEAH.
PRETTY NICE.

18:30.280 --> 18:32.402
[ NICK MULVEY'S
"FEVER TO THE FORM" PLAYING ]

18:32.402 --> 18:33.943
LISTEN, TRAV,

18:33.943 --> 18:35.575
I KNOW WE GIVE EACH OTHER
A HARD TIME,

18:35.575 --> 18:38.368
BUT TRUTH IS,

18:38.368 --> 18:40.330
I DON'T REALLY THINK
YOU'RE A NERD.

18:40.330 --> 18:41.951
WELL, THANKS.

18:41.951 --> 18:44.454
HEY, AND EVEN THOUGH I MAY
IMPLY IT OR FLAT-OUT SAY IT,

18:44.454 --> 18:46.376
I DON'T THINK YOU'RE
SHALLOW OR DUMB.

18:46.376 --> 18:48.338
THANKS.

18:48.338 --> 18:49.919
YOU TOTALLY THINK I'M A NERD.

18:49.919 --> 18:51.421
HUGE NERD. HUGE.

18:51.421 --> 18:53.423
AND YOU TOTALLY THINK
I'M SHALLOW AND DUMB, HUH?

18:53.423 --> 18:54.884
SO DUMB.

18:54.884 --> 18:57.927
BUT, UH, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

18:57.927 --> 18:59.309
[ PATS ARM ]

18:59.309 --> 19:01.761
NERD.

19:01.761 --> 19:03.683
WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?

19:03.683 --> 19:06.145
Andy: NO IDEA.

19:06.145 --> 19:10.360
[ CHUCKLES ] THAT'S WEIRD
BUT...KINDA SWEET.

19:10.360 --> 19:13.032
NO, IT ISN'T.
IT'S JUST WEIRD.

19:13.032 --> 19:15.034
CHECK IT OUT --
THREE CUTE GIRLS

19:15.034 --> 19:18.488
AND OUR BOY ADAM
THINKING ABOUT MAKING A MOVE.

19:18.488 --> 19:23.543
в™Є REASONS в™Є

19:23.543 --> 19:25.915
в™Є OH, MY FEVER TO THE FORM в™Є

19:25.915 --> 19:27.587
Adam: HOW'S IT GOING?

19:27.587 --> 19:32.462
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

19:32.462 --> 19:41.641
в™Єв™Єв™Є

19:41.641 --> 19:43.643
в™Є OH, FEVER TO THE FORM в™Є

19:43.643 --> 19:45.605
Andy: UHH! UHH!

19:46.516 --> 19:47.897
[ GRUNTS ]

19:47.897 --> 19:50.400
[ GASPS ]

19:50.400 --> 19:53.773
[ LAUGHTER ]

19:53.773 --> 19:55.575
в™Є SINGING "GIVE ME MORE" в™Є

19:55.575 --> 20:02.201
в™Є 'CAUSE YOU WERE NEVER EMPTY в™Є

20:02.201 --> 20:04.163
в™Є AND WE'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE в™Є

20:04.163 --> 20:05.585
[ LAUGHS ] ANDY'S FUN.

20:05.585 --> 20:08.087
YEAH. I LOVE
THOSE BOXER SHORTS, TOO.

20:08.087 --> 20:09.499
MM-HMM.

20:09.499 --> 20:12.542
[ LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

20:19.259 --> 20:21.341
QUITE A NIGHT. [ Shivers ]

20:21.341 --> 20:23.393
I DIDN'T -- I DIDN'T KNOW
I HAD IT IN ME.

20:23.393 --> 20:27.307
BUT WHEN DUTY CALLED, I FOUND
THE STRENGTH TO BE A HERO.

20:27.307 --> 20:29.689
I ONLY HOPE ONE DAY,

20:29.689 --> 20:32.191
BOTH OF YOU GET A CHANCE
TO KNOW HOW THAT FEELS.

20:32.191 --> 20:34.404
ACTUALLY, I WAS A LIFEGUARD
ONE SUMMER IN HIGH SCHOOL.

20:34.404 --> 20:36.696
AND I SAVED, LIKE,
15 PEOPLE FROM DROWNING.

20:36.696 --> 20:38.237
WELL, I'M A BRAIN SURGEON,

20:38.237 --> 20:40.280
SO I'VE SAVED TWO OR THREE...
HUNDRED LIVES.

20:40.280 --> 20:42.912
OH, THOSE -- THOSE --
THOSE ARE GOOD STORIES, TOO.

20:42.912 --> 20:44.324
OH, YEAH,
BUT HOW DID YOU STOP

20:44.324 --> 20:46.245
THAT GUY'S PANTS
FROM BEING PULLED DOWN?

20:46.245 --> 20:47.917
HOW DID YOU PULL THAT OFF?

20:47.917 --> 20:49.919
I DIDN'T KNOW I HAD IT IN ME,
BUT WHEN DUTY CALLED,

20:49.919 --> 20:51.831
I-I FOUND THE STRENGTH
TO BE A HERO.

20:51.831 --> 20:53.333
IT WAS ALL ADRENALINE.

20:53.333 --> 20:55.545
OR, LIKE, REPTILIAN STUFF
GOING ON IN THERE.

20:55.545 --> 20:57.176
IT WAS REALLY COOL.
YOU WEREN'T SCARED?

20:57.176 --> 21:00.970
NO, WELL...NOT SO MUCH SCARED
AS -- AS, UH, TERRIFIED.
